<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="546" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1123,1149]" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mishra, M. P. &amp; Gupta, S. N." box="[325,599,1123,1149]" pageId="7" pageNumber="546" pagination="832 - 863" refId="ref5879" refString="Mishra, M. P. &amp; Gupta, S. N. (1934) The biology of Holcocera pulverea Meyr (Blastobasidae) its predators parasites and its control. Indian Journal Agricultural Sciences, 4 (2), 832 - 863." type="journal article" year="1934">Mishra &amp; Gupta (1934)</bibRefCitation>
documented the biology of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[928,1123,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Syncola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[928,1123,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">Syncola pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Adamski, D. &amp; Pinkaew N. Nishida &amp; Deering, F." box="[1182,1436,1123,1149]" pageId="7" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref4628" refString="Adamski, D. Pinkaew N. Nishida K. &amp; Deering, F. (2020) Lepidoptera associated with cultured lac, Kerria lacca (Kerr, 1872) (Hemiptera: Kerridae), in northern Thailand. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 74 (4), 1 - 35. https: // doi. org / 10.18473 / lepi. 74 i 4. a 1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Adamski 
<emphasis box="[1293,1352,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
provided detailed descriptions and illustrations of the larva, pupa, and the adult of this species, in addition to providing details on its biology on cultured lac in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[781,884,1195,1221]" name="Thailand" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. The larva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1040,1166,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Syncola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[1040,1166,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">S. pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1428,1194,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 13−16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,1349]" captionTargetId="figure-106@6.[151,1436,381,1349]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13−16. Larva and Pupa of Syncola crypsimorpha and S. pulverea. 13, Larva of S. crypsimorpha. 14, Pupa of S. crypsimorpha. 15, Larva of S. pulverea. 16, Pupa of S. pulverea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691587/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) compared to the gray larva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[499,685,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Syncola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crypsimorpha">
<emphasis box="[499,685,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">S. crypsimorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[702,787,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 13−16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,1349]" captionTargetId="figure-106@6.[151,1436,381,1349]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13−16. Larva and Pupa of Syncola crypsimorpha and S. pulverea. 13, Larva of S. crypsimorpha. 14, Pupa of S. crypsimorpha. 15, Larva of S. pulverea. 16, Pupa of S. pulverea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691587/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). No gross differences in the pupae of both species were detected (
<figureCitation box="[260,396,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 13−16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,1349]" captionTargetId="figure-106@6.[151,1436,381,1349]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13−16. Larva and Pupa of Syncola crypsimorpha and S. pulverea. 13, Larva of S. crypsimorpha. 14, Pupa of S. crypsimorpha. 15, Larva of S. pulverea. 16, Pupa of S. pulverea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691587/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">Figs. 14, 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
